    <Note Caller="2" LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="" LastEditedBy="">
      <References>
        <Reference>02301901800044</Reference>
      </References>
      <Content>MT עִיר הַהֶרֶס &quot;City of Destruction | this expression probably is a pun on the name of the Egyptian town of Heliopolis, which, translated into Hebrew, would be עִיר הַחֶרֶס | MT {A:NIV} &quot;City of Destruction&quot; | LXX Πόλισ-ασεδεκ | {A:NJPS} &quot;Town of Heres&quot; | {A:HOTTP}-B {A:RSV} {A:NJB} {A:NRSV} {A:REB} {A:GNT} {A:CEV} &quot;City of the Sun&quot; | this latter reading is supported by most of the versions</Content>
    </Note>
